dc_title_s: Shropshyre described : the sittuation of Shrowesbury shewed with the armes of thos Earles, and other memorable things observed
dc_description_s: Relief shown pictorially. Includes historical notes and inset of "Shrowesbury." Text on verso with caption title: Shrop-shire. Book I, Chap. 37; p. 71-72; signature Rr. From: The theatre of the empire of Great Britaine ... / divided and described by John Speed. Imprinted at London : anno cum privilegio 1650 are sold by Roger Rea the elder and younger at the Golden Crosse in Cornhill near ye Exchange, [1650]
dc_publisher_s: [London] : are to be sold by Roger Rea the Elder and younger at ye Golden Crosse in Cornhill against the Exchange, [1650]
